  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and saut\u00152 until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the ginger and garlic and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes.",
    "Add the cumin, coriander, paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the millet and cook, stirring constantly, for 2-3 minutes.",
    "Add 2 cups of water and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 20-25 minutes, or until the millet is tender and the liquid has been absorbed.",
    "Fluff the pilaf with a fork and stir in the honey and chopped parsley.",
    "Serve hot."
